<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="152" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="23.[2053,2649,454,882]" pageId="23" pageNumber="152">
As understood here, this species includes, as a synonym, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1921" box="[2251,2379,651,684]" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Monodelphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="23" pageNumber="152" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="theresa">M. theresa</taxonomicName>
because specimens morphologically identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1921" box="[2508,2649,691,724]" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Monodelphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="23" pageNumber="152" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="theresa">M. theresa</taxonomicName>
were recovered nested within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1888" box="[2478,2611,730,763]" class="Mammalia" family="Didelphidae" genus="Didelphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Didelphimorphia" pageId="23" pageNumber="152" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="scalops">M. scalops</taxonomicName>
in a recent comprehensive phylogenetic analysis, indicating that these differences are actually ageand sex-related. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="152" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6685443" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6685443" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6685443/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="152" targetBox="[1440,2031,463,878]" targetPageId="23">
