<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="152" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="23.[1443,2651,888,2185]" pageId="23" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1445,1791,1835,1868]" pageId="23" pageNumber="152">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. The Tawnyheaded Opossum has a wide distribution, and it occurs in several protected areas. Some populations are considered to be declining. Fragmentation throughout the distribution of the Tawny-headed Opossums is a conservation challenge, as it is in the entire Atlantic Forest region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
